title.narrative: ADOLESCENT HEALTH

description.narrative: By 2024, adolescents from selected provinces have greater knowledge of their health through advocacy and prevention services with cross-sectoral participation., which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, children, adolescents and their families in prioritized territories receive better quality health care for their well- being and development, even in emergencies.

title.narrative: By 2024, adolescents from selected provinces have greater knowledge of their health through advocacy and prevention services withcross-sectoral participation.

description.narrative: In a scenario marked by COVID-19, with limitation of in-person activities and inter-provincial mobility, UNICEF, in alliance with MINSAP and the office of Health Promotion and Disease Prevention (ProSalud), contributed to the strengthening of the technical capacities of 615 healthcare professionals in comprehensive adolescent care, 311,498 were reached, of them 66,235 adolescents, with educational materials through the digital platforms; 2,436 adolescents and young people trained as health promoters through workshops and training efforts, with inter-sector participation, on the community level, regarding various topics related to the comprehensive health of this age group. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2022
